---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Support - Sync by PulseLab" description="Get help with Sync. FAQs, troubleshooting, and contact information.">
  <section class="pt-32 pb-8">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <a href="/sync" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[var(--primary)] mb-6 hover:underline">
        <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <path d="M19 12H5M12 19l-7-7 7-7"/>
        </svg>
        Back to Sync
      </a>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-[var(--text-dark)] mb-2">Support</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-[var(--primary)]">Sync by PulseLab</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-8">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="contact-card">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text-dark)] mb-3">Need Help?</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--text-medium)] mb-5">We're here to help you get the most out of Sync. Send us an email and we'll get back to you as soon as possible.</p>
        <a href="mailto:hello@pulselab.cc?subject=Sync%20Support" class="btn btn-primary">Email Support</a>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text-dark)] mt-12 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">Is my cycle data private?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">Yes, completely. All your data is stored locally on your device and never transmitted to our servers. We literally cannot see your information. Read our <a href="/sync/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for more details.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">Do I need to create an account?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">No. Sync works entirely without an account. This is part of our privacy-first design - no accounts means no personal information stored on servers.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">Does Sync work offline?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">Yes! Sync works completely offline. The app never needs an internet connection to function. Your data stays on your device at all times.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">How do I back up my data?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">Your Sync data is included in your iPhone backup (iCloud or local). When you restore your phone from a backup, your Sync data will be restored as well.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">How accurate are the predictions?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">Sync uses your logged cycle data to predict your fertile window and next period. The more cycles you log, the more accurate predictions become. However, please note that Sync is not a medical device and predictions should not be used as a form of birth control.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">Can I use Sync on multiple devices?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">Since Sync stores data locally and doesn't use cloud sync (for privacy), each device will have its own separate data. We recommend using Sync on your primary iPhone.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">Is there a subscription fee?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">No. Sync is a one-time purchase of $1.99. There are no subscriptions, no in-app purchases, and no ads. Pay once, use forever.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">How do I delete my data?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">You can delete individual entries within the app, use the reset option in Settings to clear all data, or simply delete the app from your device. Since we never have your data, deletion is immediate and permanent.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text-dark)] mt-12 mb-6">Getting the Most from Sync</h2>

      <div class="tips-list">
        <div class="tip-card">
          <div class="tip-icon">
            <span>üìÖ</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tip-content">
            <h3>Log Consistently</h3>
            <p>The more cycles you log, the more accurate your predictions become. Try to log the start and end of each period.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
          <div class="tip-icon">
            <span>üîî</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tip-content">
            <h3>Enable Notifications</h3>
            <p>Turn on notifications to get reminders about your upcoming period and fertile window.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
          <div class="tip-icon">
            <span>üìù</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tip-content">
            <h3>Add Notes</h3>
            <p>Use the notes feature to track symptoms, moods, or anything else you want to remember about each day.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
          <div class="tip-icon">
            <span>üíæ</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tip-content">
            <h3>Back Up Your Phone</h3>
            <p>Regular iPhone backups (to iCloud or your computer) will preserve your Sync data if you ever need to restore your device.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .contact-card {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .faq-item {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }

  .faq-question {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .faq-answer {
    color: var(--text-medium);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .faq-answer a {
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  .tips-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .tip-card {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .tip-icon {
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    background: var(--gradient);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .tip-content h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .tip-content p {
    color: var(--text-medium);
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .tip-card {
      flex-direction: column;
      text-align: center;
      align-items: center;
    }
  }
</style>
